data-triple-N3.o: "The West Bank is a landlocked territory, located in Western Asia. The West Bank shares boundaries to the west, north, and south with the state of Israel, and to the east, across the Jordan River, with the Kingdom of Jordan. The West Bank also contains a significant coastline along the western bank of the Dead Sea. The West Bank, including East Jerusalem, has a land area of 5,640km and 220km water, the northwest quarter of the Dead Sea. It has an estimated population of 2,622,544 (June 2012)."@en
